6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What weapon would you use?</span><hr size=1> I used a SCH until I was 52, then bought a Crystalline Spear (13/30).  In hindsight, it's a heavier/slower weapon than I'd ideally want, but I got it cheap and it'll do until I get RB.<br>
<br>
Depending on your race, a small dragonbone shard is an excellent weapon (DWF, HFL, GNM only).  Frozen shard is a nice primary weapon too, but a bit more expensive.  However, Ragebringer is going to be your best friend as far as getting a 15 DMG piercer goes.<br>
<br>
There are at least a dozen different threads on this subject buried in this discussion board.. Do some searching to see all the past wisdom dispensed on this topic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublusco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blusco</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/01 11:41:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12019.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What weapon would you use?</span><hr size=1> I'd say keep the slimy in your main hand and the 10/22 in your off hand until you can upgrade. As noted above, the slimy tends not to be worth much, but you could probably get a smoldering brand and some change for one (ratio is slightly better, but Brand is a much more common drop in my experience).<br>
<br>
The Brand isn't a huge upgrade though, so I wouldn't worry about taking that small of a step. Save your money and keep your eyes peeled for a bigger upgrade, or hit the Hole and keep an eye out for a Brand yourself. <p><TABLE CELLSPACING=2, CELLPADDING=2 WIDTH=90% ALIGN="center">
